<TITLE> Bail denied to HRC boss Sayeed Hossain </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 10 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Sunday denied bail chairman of HRC Group and the Jai Jai Din board of editors Sayeed Hossain Chowdhury. Dhaka metropolitan sessions judge Md Azizul Haque rejected a bail plea submitted Sunday in connection with a general diary filed against Sayeed Hossain on charges of violating Emergency Powers Rules. Police rearrested the businessman on Aug 1, shortly after he was released on bail from Dhaka Central Jail in connection with an earlier EPR case involving money laundering charges. Gulshan police had initially arrested Sayeed Hossain on May 18. Meanwhile, a motion was filed at the same court Sunday on behalf of Shamim Iskanderformer prime minister Khaleda Zia's younger brotherfor quashing the case against him on charges of amassing illegal wealth. Judge Azizul Haque fixed Sept 6 for the next hearing. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case against Shamim and his wife on May 5. He was arrested on July 18; his bail plea was rejected and he was ordered to jail on July 19. bdnew
